{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17620493","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17620493"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:43:07+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:43:07+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16629"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16629","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16629"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.17,0.37,0.09,0.37]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9320"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76340"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9320","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9320"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16629"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61849"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1315"},{"type":"tags","id":"4115"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5310"},{"type":"tags","id":"10115"},{"type":"tags","id":"10146"},{"type":"tags","id":"10604"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22093"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22502"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76340","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76340"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 24-year-old woman presents to her general practitioner requesting long-term contraception. After discussion of options, she decides to proceed with a subdermal progesterone implant (Implanon).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary mechanism of action of subdermal progesterone implants?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Prevents corpus luteum formation","Prevents implantation by thinning endometrium","Blocks fertilisation by thickening cervical mucus","Inhibits follicle stimulating hormone release","Suppresses ovulation by inhibiting luteinising hormone"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary mechanism of action of subdermal progesterone is \u003Cstrong\u003Esuppression of ovulation through inhibition of luteinising hormone\u003C/strong\u003E release. This prevents the mid-cycle surge of luteinising hormone that typically triggers ovulation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrevents corpus luteum formation\u003C/strong\u003E: the corpus luteum does not form because ovulation is prevented, rather than being directly inhibited by subdermal progesterone.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrevents implantation by thinning endometrium\u003C/strong\u003E:  subdermal progesterone does cause endometrial thinning, this serves as a secondary contraceptive mechanism rather than the primary mode of action.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocks fertilisation by thickening cervical mucus\u003C/strong\u003E: cervical mucus thickening occurs but again this is a secondary mechanism of action, not the primary action.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibits follicle stimulating hormone release\u003C/strong\u003E: subdermal progesterone predominantly affects luteinising hormone rather than follicle stimulating hormone levels.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile subdermal progesterone has multiple effects on the reproductive system, suppression of ovulation through luteinising hormone inhibition is the main contraceptive mechanism.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Subdermal progesterone implants (Implanon) work primarily by suppressing ovulation through inhibition of luteinising hormone release.","Implanon also thickens cervical mucus and thins the endometrial lining as secondary contraceptive mechanisms.","The contraceptive effect of Implanon lasts for three years."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61849"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16629"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61849","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61849"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-03T08:41:10+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-03T08:41:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9320"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76340"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},